He earnestly beseeches the Romans, that when he should be exposed in the amphitheatre‚ they would not, by their kind *but unseasonable interceffion, deprive him of the crown of glory3 and> he declares his resolution to provoke and irritate the wild beasts which might be employed as the instruments of his death ⁹³.
